<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upatofnaud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>patofnaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 1:52:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13908.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Training Pickpocket Skill</span><hr size=1> How to train Pickpockets 101.<br>
<br>
Basic rules.<br>
<br>
You can not pick undead.<br>
You can not pick magic items.<br>
You can get skill increases for picking green cons.<br>
You can pick most all bipedal mobs.<br>
You can not pick a mob over level 45 or less than 5 levels below you whichever is greater.<br>
Any mob mod that yells &quot;You will not evade me!&quot; when taunted will also rat you out with a &quot;Stop Thief! &lt;insert your name&gt;.<br>
Anything you pick DOES come from the same pool of loot obtained when that creature is killed.<br>
You can get skill increases even if you have picked a mob dry.<br>
<br>
So based on those rules, the easies way to raise pickpocketing is to aggro a green con mob, stand there and hit pick pocket every time it refreshes. <br>
<br>
Some tips...<br>
<br>
1. Chose a mob that is very low level and pickable. A_goblin_whelp, A_orc_pawn and A_gnoll_scout work great. (Your Patsy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
2. Attempt to disarm your Patsy. You want to aggro him, but you don't want to kill him.<br>
<br>
3. Run your Patsy into a remote corner of the zone. You do this so some goody goody does not kill you Patsy thinking they are helping you.<br>
<br>
4. With your Patsy targetted, turn your back on him. You do this so that an occasional Ripost does not kill him.<br>
<br>
5. Start hitting Pickpocket. You many want to also tie Instill Doubt, Sense Heading, Forage and Beg to Pickpost on a single social hotbutton.<br>
<br>
6. Go external view so you can watch your surroundings. This is so you can see if a helping Goody Goody's who will KS's you Patsy, or GM's trying to decide if they should world kick you because someone petitioned you were possibly afk and getting beat on, etc,,, is standing behind you.<br>
<br>
For extra ease, I have a wireless keyboard and my system is in my TV room, so I get set up, with external view, I turn off /shout /ooc /auction so all I see in my logs in skill ups, walk over to my recliner and watch the Sponge Bob Squarepants marrathon with the keyboard in my lap, hitting my hot key every time PP recycles.<br>
<br>
(Man I should just save some of these responses in a subdirectory and cut and paste em. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
